\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 iPhone: Direct manipulation in mobile contexts\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 The iPhone revolutionized mobile interfaces by eliminating physical buttons and replacing them with a context-adaptive touch interface. This approach is particularly relevant for field service applications as it allows the same screen real estate to serve multiple functions.\
Key lessons for field apps include using multi-touch gestures that feel natural (pinch, swipe, tap) instead of arbitrary commands, providing haptic feedback for action confirmation without requiring visual attention, and implementing a search-centered approach to quickly find functions without navigating complex menus.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 iPad: Spatial canvas for complex information\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 The iPad combines the iPhone's intuitive touch interface with a larger screen that enhances productivity without sacrificing mobility. Field service companies like McKinley Equipment have adopted iPads specifically for these qualities.\
Field applications can benefit from the iPad's approach by utilizing the expanded screen space to show complete work orders, detailed diagrams, or multiple data fields simultaneously. Split view functionality allows technicians to reference manuals while completing forms or consult messaging apps while viewing equipment specifications.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 Apple Watch: Glanceable information and quick interactions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 The Apple Watch represents an exercise in simplifying interfaces for brief interactions, making it particularly relevant for field scenarios where attention must remain on physical tasks.\
Field service applications can adopt this approach for wearable components or simplified mobile views, focusing on glanceable information that can be understood in seconds and quick actions that can be completed with minimal interaction. This is ideal for technicians who need status updates or simple controls without interrupting their workflow.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

